Key Match Events: England won 3-0 against Bosnia-Herzegovina with goals from Palmer (60' pen.), Alexander-Arnold (85'), and Kane (89').
Guehi (29') and Branthwaite (76') were notable players in the match.
Tahirovic (59') and Gazibegovic (64') were notable players for Bosnia-Herzegovina.
Pre-Game Insights: England head coach Gareth Southgate was without seven players for Sunday's training session before the match against Bosnia-Herzegovina.
This match was the first meeting between England and Bosnia-Herzegovina in a competitive or non-competitive setting.
Southgate called up a preliminary squad of 33 players for the prep period, which must be trimmed down to a minimum of 23 and a maximum of 26 players by June 7.
Harry Maguire and Luke Shaw were nursing injuries and were restricted to individual training.
Newcastle United winger Anthony Gordon was not present due to an ankle injury.
Harry Kane participated in the practice session despite a back problem.
Jude Bellingham, Phil Foden, Kyle Walker, and Kobbie Mainoo were unavailable due to recent club commitments.
